def _get_time_bins(self, ax):
    if not isinstance(ax, DatetimeIndex):
        raise TypeError(
            "axis must be a DatetimeIndex, but got "
            f"an instance of {type(ax).__name__}"
        )

    if len(ax) == 0:
        binner = labels = DatetimeIndex(data=[], freq=self.freq, name=ax.name)
        return binner, [], labels

    # Start from the first actual timestamp instead of relying on 'ax.min()'
    first = ax[0]
    last = ax[-1] + self.freq
    if self.base is not None:
        first = self.base.apply(first)
        last = self.base.apply(last)

    # Create bins and labels using DatetimeIndex
    binner = labels = DatetimeIndex(data=[], freq=self.freq, name=ax.name)
    bins = binner.asi8
    labels = np.array([Timestamp(val, freq=self.freq) for val in bins])
    bins = lib.generate_bins(np.asarray(ax), np.asarray(bins, dtype="M8[ns]"), closed=self.closed, right=self.closed == "right")
    
    return binner, bins, labels
